>>15249489
Not in order,since by doing one thing you usually start getting ideas for everything else:
-come up with beginning, middle and end
-come up with characters to populate the story with: Who they are, What they do, a quirk they have (something that motivates them, a secret they have, etc.)
-figure out the rules of the world they operate in (realistic, fanatasy, sci-fi, etc.)
-figure out how the characters you came up would logically get from point A to point B and then to C, while operating within the personalities and world you gave them, then write it down
-jump between the earlier points and continue to refine them until you have something you are not ashamed to make others read (crying about how your cake is not as good looking as someone else's is permissible for a bit, but do no wallow in it)

>tl;dr
give yourself some 'restrictions' to operate under while writing
